              <span slot="content">Critics Consensus

Fantastic Beasts and Where to Find Them recaptures the wonder of the Wizarding World with heart, humor, and dazzling imagination, delivering a magical adventure that feels both fresh and timeless.

Director David Yates brings a vibrant new era of magic to life, trading Hogwarts for a richly detailed 1920s New York filled with charm and danger. Eddie Redmayne is outstanding as Newt Scamander, whose kindness and awkward sincerity make him an instantly lovable hero. The magical creatures are endlessly inventive, balancing spectacle with genuine emotion, while the ensemble cast adds warmth, humor, and depth. Funny, heartfelt, and visually breathtaking, Fantastic Beasts and Where to Find Them expands the Wizarding World in thrilling fashion while capturing the same sense of awe that made the original series unforgettable.</span>
